>So who is O’Connor’s replacement going to be?</strong> It’s not yet known, but whoever they choose will have to strike a difficult balance between maintaining ratings and satisfying the traditionalist fanbase.</p> <p><strong>Perhaps the new editor could organise a huge cake sale in a barn, and then burn the barn down? </strong>Your idea will be passed on to the relevant department.</p> <p><strong>Do say:</strong> “This job would be perfect for anyone with experience in radio drama, a deep knowledge of the show’s history and a real drive to innovate.”</p> <p><strong>Don’t say: </strong>“Except you, Helen darling. You need to rest.”</p>","internalOctopusCode":"11275051","productionOffice":"UK","newspaperEditionDate":"2016-02-22T00:00:00Z","hasStoryPackage":"false","internalPageCode":"2460145","internalRevision":"71","publication":"The Guardian","trailText":"Sean O’Connor is leaving Ambridge and heading east after a semi-controversial stint that brought death and chaos to rural Britain. Fancy his job?","allowUgc":"false","lang":"en","headline":"High drama in The Archers as editor leaves for Walford","isInappropriateForSponsorship":"false","commentable":"true","firstPublicationDate":"2016-02-21T17:30:33Z","secureThumbnail":"https://media.guim.co.uk/aa3daacc5e709ec7c42611937a5ec0ff0321b068/0_118_4284_2573/140.jpg","liveBloggingNow":"false","main":"<figure class=\"element element-image\" data-media-id=\"aa3daacc5e709ec7c42611937a5ec0ff0321b068\"> <img src=\"http://media.guim.co.uk/aa3daacc5e709ec7c42611937a5ec0ff0321b068/0_0_4284_2856/1000.jpg\" alt=\"Rural bliss … Charlotte Martin and Brian Hewlett as Susan and Neil Carter. \" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption> <span class=\"element-image__caption\">Rural bliss … Charlotte Martin and Brian Hewlett as Susan and Neil Carter. </span> <span class=\"element-image__credit\">Photograph: Gary Moyes/BBC</span> </figcaption> </figure>","shortUrl":"http://gu.com/p/4gqtd","wordcount":"409","shouldHideA